Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_tracks(25.10)                                      report_tracks(25.10)

Name
       report_tracks - Reports track definitions for each layer

Syntax
       report_tracks

       [-help]

       [-prefer_only]

       Reports  track  definitions  for  each  layer. The output is in the DEF
       TRACKS format. This command can be used after the floorplan is  created
       or  after using the add_tracks command to see exactly which tracks were
       created.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each report_tracks parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_tracks.

       -prefer_only
              Reports  track  definitions  only for the preferred direction of
              each layer.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command reports the track definitions  for  each
                layer:

                report_tracks

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal6 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 1503 STEP 1980 LAYER Metal6 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal5 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal5 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal4 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal4 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal3 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal3 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal2 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal2 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal1 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal1 ;

              * The  following  command reports the track definitions only for
                the preferred direction of each layer:

                report_tracks -prefer_only

                TRACKS X 660 DO 1503 STEP 1980 LAYER Metal6 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal5 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal4 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal3 ;

                TRACKS X 660 DO 2255 STEP 1320 LAYER Metal2 ;

                TRACKS Y 560 DO 2657 STEP 1120 LAYER Metal1 ;

